|12,72
     A Variable Declaration placeholder appears in the VAR section of a
Pascal program or subprogram.  To begin filling in the placeholder, enter
a name that you want to use as a variable.  After this, you will be asked
to enter the Type of the variable and a comment describing what the
variable will be used for.
|mFor more, choose
|iDo nothing,nop
|iNames,Hpclass/name
|iTypes,Hpclass/type
|iForm of Variable Declarations,Hpnode/variable_dec
